The '''8th constituency of the Bas-Rhin''' is a French legislative [[Constituency (France)|constituency]] in the [[Bas-Rhin]] [[departments of France|''département'']].

==Description==

The 8th constituency of Bas-Rhin covers the Northern most portion of the Departement, bordering  (Germany) to both the east and north. It includes the small town of [[Wissembourg]] on the German border as well as the surrounding countryside.

It has been a bastion of the conservative right since the inception of the [[French Fifth Republic|Fifth Republic]]. It won easily by the [[Union for a Popular Movement|UMP]] in the First round of the [[2012 Election]] with the National Front coming a distant second some 16,000 votes behind [[Frédéric Reiss]].

